-------------------------------------------------
Installation and Configuration of SSID
-------------------------------------------------

------------
Installation
------------

1) Install MySQL, Apache, Ruby (1.9.2), and bundler (a ruby gem; 1.1.2) 

2) Download SSID from the GitHub repository:
	 https://github.com/WING-NUS/SSID

3) Download MySQL Connector/J version 5.1.13 from
	 http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/connector/
   - Put the downloaded file "mysql-connector-java-5.1.13-bin.jar"
     into the directory: 
       - lib/java/programs/lib
   - If you wish to recompile any of SSID's jar files, you will also
     need to copy "mysql-connector-java-5.1.13-bin.jar" to the following
     directories:
	     - lib/java/PlagiarismDetection/lib
	     - lib/java/DBSCAN/lib

-------------
Configuration
-------------

1) Copy config/database.yml.mysql-template to
	 config/database/database.yml. Alternatively, use the sqlite3 template.

2) Modify database.yml with your database settings

3) Run bundler to install the necessary gems (including rails) from the root
   directory of SSID:
     bundle install 

3) Execute the following command in the root directory of SSID:
	 rake db:migrate RAILS_ENV="production"

4) Configure Apache to serve web requests to SSID
